inn1.comm: full outside off stump, goes for a drive and gets a thick inside edge into the leg side
good line outside off, Gayle chops down on it and finds short cover
touch more width, Gayle guides this down to third man
can't adjust to the right hander, fires this down the leg side and it's the first extra of the day
better from Broad, gets back outside off stump, left alone
slight hint of swing, but it carries at ankle height through to Matt Prior
fuller outside off, good length, Simmons shoulders arms again
pushed across the left hander, carries quite nicely through to the keeper
good line from Anderson, on middle and Gayle defends to the on side
tucked off middle to square leg, can't beat the fielder
well bowled by Anderson, beats Gayle on the inside edge as he comes forward but it doesn't carry through on the full to Prior
drives up to mid-off, sets off for a sharp single and Gayle isn't exactly moving swiftly but still manages to make it
well bowled, squares Simmons up a touch as he defends back to the bowler
that's more like it from Gayle, swung hard down the ground past mid-on with real force
goes through midwicket this time, not out of the middle but he's so strong that it still races away to the rope
great comeback from Broad, bounce and carry outside off as Gayle is beaten playing forward...Prior takes it around his shoulder
driven into the covers, nicely timed but goes straight to cover
short and wide outside off, slashed away up and over backward point, poor delivery from Broad and Gayle wasn't going to miss out on that
goes round the wicket, gets away with this one, still too much width but Gayle cuts it straight to the point fielder
full on the stumps, turned sweetly down to mid-on

that's out, superb delivery from Anderson, hint of movement away to Simmons who gets an healthy edge through to Prior...nice bowling, pace and bounce on that one and it was too much for Simmons who was trying to guide it to third man
lbw appeal first ball, struck on the pads but it's going down the leg side although that's how England want to attack Sarwan early and failed to manage during the Test series
off the mark in nice style, opens the face and guides it between backward point and cover, outfield is quick and they come back for two
bouncer, first of the day, and Sarwan ducks underneath...more bounce from Anderson's end
worked out to midwicket
full outside off, goes to drive but gets a thick bottom edge which bobbles backward of point
full on the stumps, pushed straight down the ground and mid-on can't get across to stop the single
well bowled, awkward bounce on off stump, takes the shoulder of the bat and goes out to backward point
goes for the leg-stump yorker, Gayle gets bat on it and it races past the leg slip who had no chance of stopping it standing so close
back on off stump, pushed out to short cover
hint of late movement into Gayle, he squirts it into the gap at midwicket and keeps the strike

got him! Anderson has his second as Gayle drags into his stumps, massive strike for England. That was a loose shot from the captain as he tried to guide it to third man with an angled bat and was defeated by a hint of low bounce
well bowled, certainly some extra bounce as well at times, Chanderpaul plays it down into the leg side
worked from off stump into the leg side, Anderson fields in his follow through
worked out to square leg
steered off the outside edge, Strauss makes a good save as he dives to his left at second slip
pushed into the off side, another impressive and successful over from Anderson who has given England a fine start
floaty half volley from Broad, outside off and Sarwan flays it through the off side...Broad not having a good day so far
better length, on off stump, defended into the leg side
full outside off again from Broad, he's feeding Sarwan's drive but this time Bopara makes a good save at extra cover
pushed down the ground, fielded by mid-off
full on middle and off, forced back to Broad who stoops low in his follow through to field
drifts down the leg side this time, there was a noise but umpire Duncan gives it as wide
a cutter outside off, Sarwan chops it out to backward point who stops any runs
worked from off stump through midwicket, good use of the wrists from Chanderpaul and he collects a couple
guided down to third man, shorter outside off and Chanderpaul played it nicely
positive drive but picks out mid-off
touch short outside off, driven from the back foot to point
good bouncer, over off stump, Sarwan sways his head out of the line
good line on off stump, defended into the off side to end another tight over
starts with a good one outside off, Chanderpaul plays and misses, doesn't carry to Prior
driven up to mid-off
outside off, going across Chanderpaul who leaves alone
finds the outside edge, squirted down to third man past the lone slip
well bowled, on off stump and Sarwan gets squared up with the outside edge flying wide of backward point as he tried to work through the leg side...goes wide of third man for a couple
cut out to backward point, Sarwan might feel he missed out on that one
outside off, driven into the covers
worked off middle, picks out square leg
short this time and well played by Chanderpaul, he just swivelled on it and helped the ball past square leg with enough timing for a boundary
driven wide of mid-off, can't beat Pietersen but they get an easy single
shapes back into Sarwan who angles the face and plays to backward point
runs this away down to third man
good length, forcing him back, and it's nudged to leg
tries to whip it through mid-on but can't time it
fuller delivery and stroked out to cover
left alone outside off
on leg stump and nudged to nowhere
left alone outside off
nicely flicked to leg with a wristy turn
really good line and length - nice and full, swinging back onto Chanderpaul's off stump
given a bit of width here and Chanderpaul pats it down to third man
angled down to third man
squeezed out to the off side
angled out to the off side
stands back and smacks it out to the off side
dropped out to the off side
swings this to mid-on
edged through the vacant slip for four! Probably wouldn't have carried in fact, and I'm even inclined to think he played it deliberately. Anyway. It's four
good line outside off, and left alone
short of a length and pull-paddled around the corner. This pitch is absurdly slow; batsmen have enough time to make a cup of tea after the bowler wangs it down
goes for a drive and gets an inside edge to leg
on his legs, flicked to fine leg - where Mascarenhas misfields. But they don't take two
down the leg side, off his pads
fullish length, driven to mid-off
very full and driveable length. Chanderpaul bunts it back powerfully to Broad who fields it comfortably in his follow-through
and it's defended out to the off side
pushed out to the off side
straighter delivery this time, nudged through midwicket for a hastily run single
shorter this time, and four! Chanderpaul was so quick onto that, pulling it powerfully through midwicket
defended out to the off side
comes forward, defending to cover
turned to leg
flattish ball on middle, stroked to mid-on
prods forward, poking it to cover. Good length from Batty
touch shorter, rocks back and strokes it out to the off side
flighted on middle, drilled down the ground
nicely bowled. Flicked back to the bowler
good length again, and Chanderpaul can only nurdle it back to the bowler
short, wide but he escapes punishment thanks to the short mid-off
turned to mid-on
outside off, carefully flipped to long-on
flicked to leg
pushed back to the bowler
flicked through midwicket
nicely flighted and Sarwan works it to leg
nurdled to the leg side
again turned to leg
on middle, and it's flicked to short midwicket

much too short but - wow! Absolutely stunning fielding from Anderson. Sarwan pulled it over midwicket and Anderson dived on the rope, saved four - and aware that the momentum might carry him and the ball over for four, flicked it back to the waiting fielder. Top stuff
flicked to leg
defended out to the of side
a touch fuller, driven through mid-on this time
down the leg side and Sarwan works it to Batty at a wideish long-on
slapped to cover
driven down the ground
cracked out to cover off the back foot
short, wide and cut
long-on collects as it's stroked out on the front foot
worked to midwicket to bring up their fifty partnership
too short - way too short and wide. You can't bowl there to Sarwan in this kind of form. It's hammered for four
driven to long-on
nudged to leg
excellent, disciplined line just on the off stump. Chanderpaul pats in defence
turned back to the bowler
Prior's dropped Chanderpaul. Oh dear. Oh double, triple dear. A loose slap by Chanderpaul, thin outside edge which hammered into Prior's fingers which never moved.
driven down the ground
short of a length, punched out through cover
worked to long-on
pushed back to Batty
nice and full and Chanders can only drive it back to the bowler. Good line
ever so slightly wider, Chanders opens the face to point
skips down the pitch and strokes to Pietersen at long-off
shot! He timed that brilliantly. A skip down the pitch, flicking it loftily over midwicket for six
flicked just wide of Collingwood at short midwicket. Only just!
bang! Nothing complicated about that at all. He leans back and absolutely thumps it over extra cover
fuller ball turned to leg
cautiously nudged to leg
punched to short mid-off
fuller ball spearing into his legs, it's flicked to mid-on
driven to long-off
worked to leg and Anderson fields incredibly quickly. He's always been good in the outfield, but he's added a new feature to his fielding in being able to throw "on the run". Quality fielder now
uppishly driven just wide of the man at cover!
easily worked to leg
punched to the leg side
dropped out to the off side and there's Sarwan's fifty. Another one! Quite incredible form. It's his 32nd ODI fifty and England really don't know how to get him out. 58 balls for this latest fifty
squeezed to mid-off
dropped out to the off side
flicked back to the bowler
nudged to leg but there's no timing
turned off his pads behind square. Well placed
back cut to third man where Ian Bell - who seems to have put on a bit of weight, to say the least - fields
defended on the back foot
tossed up outside off, turned to leg
not quite timed this like his other boshes, but he's got enough on it for four. Skipped down the pitch and wellied it over the top for four
short, back-cut down to third man for four. Immense skill. This really is a magical knock by Sarwan
jumps back and strokes it to long-on
flicked back to the bowler
comfortable tip-and-run flick to long-on
a little late on it, but nevertheless flicked it to leg
that's well bowled, swinging back a touch on Sarwan who drives back to Collingwood
squared up here! Too early on it, and it falls short of the short mid-off
punched back to the bowler
worked to mid-on
pushed out to the off side
on middle-and-off, pushed out to mid-off
turned to leg
cut down to third man
opens the face and angles it to third man
Sarwan aims for an ugly cross-batted slap over midwicket but can only smudge it to mid-on. That was the sort of shot I excelled with
left alone outside off
flicked down to long leg
turned into the gap at midwicket
pushed down the ground, cover can't get across in time to prevent the single
turned out through square leg, Sarwan thinks about the second but Harmison does some good work in the deep
worked from outside off to the man at midwicket
finds the gap on the leg side this time, deep square keeps it to a single
tries to work the off-side gap but finds the man at cover
tight line on off stump, can't beat backward point on this occasion
comes across his crease and works it through the leg side into the deep
chopped away to Collingwood at backward point
driven firmly down to long off
worked off the stumps again into the big gap on the leg side, comfortable single to end the over
pushed back to the bowler
good line from Collingwood, hard to get away at his pace and turned out to midwicket
finds the gap down to long on this time
gives himself a touch of room but the drive goes straight to cover
bunted down the ground to long on...happy to tick over in singles at the moment
worked away down to long leg
opens the face, runs it to backward point and it's a tight single as Collingwood takes aim and he hits Chanderpaul on the wrist with the throw
gives himself room again and makes decent contact with a big swing through the off side, not quite middled but placed well enough for a couple out to deep cover
worked down the ground, very straight, but Pietersen at long on gets round in time to stop the second
slower ball on middle, nicely turned off the stumps and well placed for two...takes Chanderpaul through to his half century which is cheered loudly by the home support
tucked off the body down to long leg
ooh, nearly gets an inside edge into his stumps but instead collects a single to long leg
punched down the ground off the back foot
brings out the sweep to the medium pace, swung around down to fine leg
pushed down to long off...all fairly easy for West Indies at the moment
low full toss, swings a touch as Chanderpaul tries to work to the leg side and finishes up getting a leading edge down to long off
yorker this time, dug out to the off side
driven off the back foot down to long off
goes for the cut and misses, but Prior can't collect and gives away more byes
beats short midwicket and gets a single down the ground
goes down to sweep, takes the pad and beats Prior down the leg side racing away to the boundary
chopped away to Batty at backward point
terrific save from Batty at backward point, he's up and throws in one movement and almost beats Chanderpaul's dive back...good work
worked neatly off the stumps out to deep square-leg
down the leg side, takes the pad and Prior makes the save
full outside leg stump, worked into the gap at midwicket
follows Sarwan towards leg stump, fired into the pads and bobbles into the off side

and Anderson strikes, Sarwan started to shuffle around the crease but the bowler held his nerve and an attempted drive loops to mid-off on the edge of the circle...very important breakthrough for England
defended into the off side
driven on the up out to cover on the edge of the circle
goes for the cut, ball keeps a little low and he misses
opens his shoulders, lofted high over mid-on and goes two bounces over the rope
slower-ball bouncer outside off, Chanderpaul misses his cut
worked off the stumps, placed between square and long leg with the right power for two...Broad isn't happy
nurdled from off stump into the square-leg area
tucked off middle stump out to midwicket who is on the edge of the circle
some late swing as Anderson goes very full, driven powerfully down to mid-off
there we go, Chanderpaul goes across his stumps and works it past short fine leg...no one out on the leg-side boundary and Chanderpaul knew it
and again, this time he swings hard to midwicket
comes round the wicket, Chanderpaul goes over the top of square leg for another boundary...he plays these overs so well
back over the wicket, strays down the leg side, pressure telling on Anderson
tries to sweep this, taken on the toe of the bat and it runs behind to the keeper
low full toss on the toes, worked out to deep midwicket where Bopara fumbles and they come back for two...which they always doing anyway
big shout from Broad, but he bowled it from very wide and it's going down the leg side...ball flies to backward point
the field is set deep on the leg side so Chanderpaul goes over mid-off, just beating a great leap from Collingwood and collects another boundary
goes down the leg side, Broad not happy with the call but he just needs to get on and bowl
chopped away into the off side, can't beat point
what a shot from Chanderpaul, that is amazing, he brings out the reverse sweep and hammers a good length ball past point...eat your heart out Kevin Pietersen
dragged down wide outside off this time, Broad's getting himself in a real state at the moment...he's not having a great day
he's losing it here, very wide of off stump again, Chanderpaul can barely reach it
third in a row, goes for the slower ball and it's too wide again...Broad not sure what to do and major problems here for Andrew Strauss
wide of the stumps, but close enough for the drive but backward point prevents any runs
opens the face and runs it to short third man...ends a long and expensive over
swing and a miss outside off
very short and pulled through midwicket
pulled on the front foot out to deep midwicket
smashed to mid-off who wings down a shy at the non-striker's stumps

full toss above waist height, but Chanderpaul's pulled it - straight down Harmison's throat at fine leg! What a catch from the big man, who keeps himself inside the line. But, drama here - Chanderpaul's asking the umpire why that wasn't a no-ball, as it was above waist height. And he signals it was a no-ball! Blimey. Drama. Correct decision made. Harmison's catch was an absolute snorter taking it well over his head to save six
goes for a pull but can't time it
pushed out to the off side for a hasty two
pulled into the deep and Anderson pulls off another quality save, getting his body behind the line and scooping it up
four! Another brilliant reverse-sweep for four down to third man (or fine-leg...depending on your view). And he hammered it!
goes for a back cut
got him! Powerfully lofted but straight to Pietersen at long-on who takes a fine, tumbling catch to his right
slower ball on leg stump, pushed back to the bowler
nobbled to leg
a floaty little number on middle stump which is nudged to mid-on
off the mark with a nudged two through the on-side
down the leg side and again he leans on it through midwicket for a couple
solid forward defensive
good line outside off which Bravo prods to a deepish mid-off. They jog a single
nudged back to Collingwood
good length, he goes back to cut but it's too close to him
stroked back to the bowler
pushed just to the bowler's left
crashed out to the off side
a leg-side delivery flicked - guess? - to the leg side. Mascarenhas sets off in hot pursuit but can't prevent the single
down the leg side but he escapes being clattered for six, as he should have been, as he can only roll his wrists on it to send the ball to short fine leg
bunted to deep mid-on
short and wide and Bravo cracks this off the back foot quite extravagantly, just passed Bopara at cover
stroked to mid-off who shies at the stumps, misses by a country mile, and they get an overthrow
clunked out to the off side. Good stop
nicely squirted down to third man
full toss worked to mid-on
flicked around the corner but there's no timing
beautifully lofted over long-off. Really elegant, with a full swing of the bat. The ball, however, was sitting up and literally begging to be hit
misses out on this cut. For once, Prior's glovework is sharp
full and quick, flicked to mid-on
a single to mid-on
full toss, squeezed through midwicket
on the off stump, turned to Shah at long-on
outside off and stroked to long-off
flicked through midwicket
slower ball, wide of the off stump and the crowd all deflate their cheers as he can't get a single
flicked to leg and there's his hundred! His 10th ODI hundred and he's done it at his home ground who, to a man and woman, are standing. It's quite a sight
goes inside out and drives out to long-off
well wide of the off stump

bouncer and pulled over midwicket - but what a catch by Paul Collingwood! Bravo absolutely nailed this pull and Collingwood back-peddled, taking the ball with both hands over his head while falling backwards. And he does well to stay inside the rope. Outstanding skill
dropped out to the off side
stroked to mid-off
outside off, pushed back to the bowler
tries to clatter it through the covers
well that's a bit of a poor shot really. He stood with both feet pointing down the pitch and tried to scoop it very fine over the keeper's head, but could only spoon it straight to a short fine-leg
straight ball worked to mid-on
good, straight ball on off stump which squares him up a bit
flicked through midwicket for a couple
banged to long-off
brilliant. His third reverse-swept four and he plays it so well
firmly stroked to mid-off
a full toss outside off but he toe-ends it and busts his bat. A replacement is called for
another reverse-hit, more of a paddle this time. And mistimed, too. Super attempt though
muscularly slapped! Wow - that nearly killed Mascarenhas. He stood tall and just slapped it past him. No chance of catching that
another powerful and crunching bunt to long-on
dug out to the off side and he steals a single
nudged to leg
whipped to long-on and they get two
got him. Good, straight off-cutter which raps him on the back pad as he attempted to swing it over midwicket
bowled him! Collingwood's on a hat-trick here, bowling Miller with a lovely little off-cutter which kept a touch low. Poor stroke though from Miller trying to cut it
outside off and flicked to leg, No hat-trick this time
flipped to midwicket
very wide indeed and Chanderpaul, a little crippled with cramp in the legs, can only just reach it
attempts to crash this over extra cover but ends up slicing it to third man
stands tall and pulls it powerfully into the ground. Mascarenhas swooped and tried to get a finger on it as the ball shattered the non-striker's stumps, but couldn't quite manage it
flicked to leg
plays and misses outside off
carved out to cover just for a single

inn2.comm: starts on off stump, pushed out into the leg side
bit more force in this shot but it still just rolls out to midwicket
dropped a tough a chance at second slip, Strauss forces off the back foot and gets a thick edge to Sammy's left...went one-handed, but couldn't hold on and parries it down to third man
good length on off stump, defended back down the pitch
lovely on drive from Bopara, everything technically right about that as he pushes through the line and opens his account in fine style
drags the length back, defended down to mid-off
short of a length, tight on off stump, defended down to mid-off
fuller and on off stump, defended carefully into the covers
well bowled, hint of shape back into Strauss who punches firmly back to the bowler
nicely cut away off the back foot, just evades the diving backward point and third man does the fielding
on off stump, defended back down the pitch
nicely worked away from Bopara, a quick turn of the wrists takes it quickly towards fine leg where Devon Smith, on as a sub for Chanderpaul, makes a good save
leg side from Baker but Bopara can only clip it to the man at forward square-leg, went in the air for quite a long way
width outside off stump, Bopara stands tall and gets over the ball to cut it square through the off side
on leg stump again, takes the pad out to square leg
better line and length, draws Bopara onto the front front and he defends down into the gully area
pushed into the leg side, maybe kept a fraction low
dropped into the leg side in front of mid-on, a well judged single from Bopara to keep the strike
swinging away outside off, left alone
stands tall and turns this into the leg side
defended into the off side, good line from Edwards, no width offered
too wide this time, swinging away outside off and an easy call for Aleem Dar
another strong cut from Bopara, actually more of a back-foot drive and it races away through backward point wide of third man
drives into the off side but without any timing
driven firmly into the off side, steady start from England
worked off the body down to long leg
defended back down the pitch
there's the breakthrough, Baker gets Bopara to drag into his stumps, a bit of a loose drive but he didn't get to the pitch...a shame as he'd started brightly, but that's a good boost for West Indies
gets away with a boundary first ball, thick outside edge flies past slip and away to third man...no one catching at second slip, but it might not have carried anyway
firm drive back to the bowler, Baker swoops down in his follow through and makes a good save
opens the face and defends square on the off side
poor line, down the leg side, flicked away to fine leg
back of a length, nicely whipped through midwicket as he uses the pace on the ball...Pollard chases it down and seems in some pain after his slide
dragged down short and wide, Pietersen chases it but that doesn't stop the wide being called
good ball, shaping in on off stump, pushed back down the off side
banged in short, goes for the pull and doesn't make contact as the ball cannons off his rib cage, beats the keeper and slip down to the boundary
nice looking back-foot drive, sends the ball rifling down to mid-off
quick single down to mid-on, the man there is a little slow and it is fairly comfortable in the end
goes for a booming drive, comes off a thick inside half of the bat and rolls down to mid-on
outside off, Pietersen goes into a flowing drive but picks out mid off
straight ball, whipped right from middle and off stump but straight to Bravo at square leg
more leg side this time, flicked away down to long leg
wide outside off, Strauss leans into a positive drive but can't find the gap past mid off
worked into the leg side, again can't find the gap and that's another good over from Baker
gets away with one here, tempted into a big drive and gets a thick inside edge that races past his stumps down to fine leg

gone this time! Edwards wins the battle in convincing style. Pietersen went to play off the back foot and gets another inside edge, this time it crashes into leg stump and that's a huge wicket for West Indies
outside off, left alone, and that doesn't carry through to Ramdin...variation in bounce from Edwards
defended up to mid-on
comes forward, good line on off stump, defended into the covers
wide outside off, left alone to end a good over from Edwards
good line on off stump, defended back down the pitch
pushes outside off stump, ball stops a little but its safely played down in front of point
goes for the pull, doesn't make contact as the delivery doesn't get up, a dangerous shot on a pitch keeping low
comes forward and pushes into the off side, parried away by Bravo so it turns into an easy single
nicely bowled, extra bounce outside off and Shah pushes hard...the thick edge flies through the empty slip cordon and Edwards makes a hash of the save down at third man to give away a boundary
slammed away through the covers, a powerful cover drive against a wide delivery and Shah just frees his arms and gives it everything
well bowled, Strauss tries to turn this to the leg side and gets an outside edge that lands short of backward point
nicely guided away this time, opens the face and directs it past Gayle at first slip...was a slow ball from Edwards and Strauss played it all along the ground for his first boundary
short and wide, slashed away over the slips for consecutive boundaries...Gayle clearly not happy with that ball from Edwards
goes straighter and is turned away through midwicket
driven firmly out to short cover
turned from off stump out to midwicket...good over for England
down the leg side for just the on
spearing in on middle stump, nudged to leg
squeezed out to point
that's a thumping four from Strauss. Admittedly, too full and wide but Strauss leaned into an exquisite cover drive
another drive, this time sliced to third man
stroked to Gayle at short-extra
down the leg side
flicked off his pads
wider and a slower delivery cut out to the off side
better delivery on off stump which he angles down to third man
cuts back in just outside the off stump and he misses
cut out to point
flicked to midwicket
well wide and rightly wided
keeps very low outside off
straight, and smartly whipped ... but straight to midwicket
holds up on him a bit, but he nevertheless drills it to mid-off
angled to third man
well bowled, cutting back into the right hander
back cut to third man
on the back foot, defended
outside off, Shah guides it behind square
on middle stump he works it through midwicket
horrible shot. Tries to chop it to third man and nearly does a KP by chopping it onto his stumps
defended nicely off the back foot
clipped to leg and Shah, for once, steals a quick and safe single
great timing. Less good placement. He picks out midwicket with a flick
worked to midwicket again
comes forward to defend
another forward defensive to mid-on
straightish ball nudged to leg
squeezed out to the off side
huge shout for lbw as Bravo delivers a lovely slow off-cutter, deceiving Strauss, but it pitched outside leg
flicked to leg
angling into Shah's leg stump, he strokes to mid-on
good straight ball, defended
angled to backward point, and still there's no run
steals the strike with a drive to long-on
shuffles into a pushy drive to mid-off
Strauss waits on the back foot and guides to mid-off
cuts back into Strauss who nudges
punched to cover
angled to third man
cut to third man
punched off the back foot to mid-off
flicked to leg
played and missed to a slower ball
driven out to deep cover
stroked out nicely on the front foot
outside off and manufactured to cover
paddled for a single through midwicket
clips this to mid-on
and he's dropped him, has Sammy. Little slower-ball-cutter which deceived Strauss, the ball ballooning up through his hands
keeps low outside off
angled out to point
whipped off his pads
good ball on off stump, which again Shah defends
ooh, close! Shah came forward and reverse-spun it over his stumps. Bravo nearly ruptures himself in excitement as the ball evades the stumps
got him this time! A quicker ball sliding into Shah - beautiful bowling from Bravo and up goes the finger
clipped to deep midwicket for a single
very nicely turned to leg with a flick of the wrists
bowled him! Another tentative prod by an England batsman but a fine ball which swung back between bat and pad, clipping the off stump
patted away to the off side
angled to backward point who does brilliantly to stop it, but his throw is comically wide. And I mean comically wide
defended on the back foot
solidly forward onto the front foot by Prior
good length forcing him back, and a tight line. Defended
and again, another off-cutter which is blocked
wild and woolly down the leg side
well bowled! Another slower ball, a little leg-cutter which completely beats Strauss
but this one is wide of the off stump
punched off the back foot and cover mis-fields
flicked to mid-on
really well stopped by Pollard at mid-on, diving to his right to save a firmly-clipped drive from Prior
driven to extra cover
short of a length, hurrying him into a defensive
fuller length which is pushed to mid-on
too straight for Prior to do anything with. All he manages is a defensive
ooh, driven back to the bowler and only just short of him. He gives Prior a glare. He knows there's a battle on here

got him! The grinning Duncan raises his finger as Prior shuffled back to one which kept low, and he got a very thin edge through to Ramdin who also ensured he kept low, taking a fine catch. A really super catch
cut to third man
his feet concreted, Mascarenhas drives and gets a thick inside edge onto his boot
late swing into the right-hander. Bravo mouths "ooooooh"
stroked out to the off side
cut out to the off side

neat stroke, lifting this off cutter from outside off. Though, his hand came off the bat which rather suggests he was in no control of it whatsoever. So I'm doing him far too great a service. Anyway - four runs it is
slightly slower ball on the off stump to which he comes forward to defend
cuts this hard where backward point pulls off a useful save
cut out to the off side
rapped on the pads but it's going down leg
driven back to the bowler
cut out to point
outside off and hammered
clumped to mid-off
flipped for yet another dull single
nicely turned off his toes through midwicket. Simmons fields superbly
flicked off his pads
shorter ball, mis-pulled over midwicket
defended out to cover-point and Strauss nearly made a complete mess of it, but got back in time
good, tight line blocked off the back foot
swivels onto a pull to Simmons at deep midwicket
prods it to long-off for another walked-single
chops it down
uppishly worked to mid-on, but it's perfectly safe innit
angled to third man
opens the face and squeezes a single to short third man
nicely dabbed away by Strauss, played it very late outside off down towards third man
same again from Strauss but this time it goes a little squarer and straight to the short third man
on the pads, pushed into the leg side
worked off the stumps to Gayle at midwicket who prevents the single despite not moving at full capacity
flicked round to short fine leg, Strauss has to sprint to complete the run but makes it as the throw is wide
keeps a little low on middle, pushed out to midwicket
cut away through the off side to the sweeper
loose shot outside off, a nothing dab from Mascarenhas as he tries to find third man
swings harder at this one, the ball scoots low under his bat and is called wide as well
better line, keeps low and shapes in from outside off, defended back down the pitch
hardly any pace off the surface makes it hard to force the ball away, Mascarenhas slaps this down to mid-off but meant to play it squarer
tries to turn it into the leg side, takes the body into the off side
hint of width, cut away but can't beat short third man
driven through the off side, an easy two as it goes wide of the sweeper
pushed back down the pitch
short and whipped away through midwicket
full on off stump, turned away to midwicket
goes for the reverse sweep but doesn't make contact
driven in the air back over the bowler, was well clear of Pollard
pushed out through midwicket as he takes his bottom hand off the bat
turned away off the pads out to deep square-leg
moves across the stumps, misses his swipe and it's called wide
chopped away to backward point
goes for a paddle sweep from outside off, doesn't make contact and this innings isn't really going anywhere
very wide outside off, good take from Ramdin to prevent further extras
turned off middle and out to deep square leg
turned out to midwicket and that brings up Strauss's half century
pushed into the off side
worked down to long on, they run hard but it's just a single
comes across outside off, turns it down to short fine leg and they scamper a single
ticking over in singles, this one goes along the ground through midwicket
comes down the pitch, gets an inside into his pads which rolls into the off side and they can't get a run
driven down to long off
pushed into the off side, sharp single to mid-off but comfortable enough in the end
wide outside off, Mascarenhas frees his arms but can only find long off
on leg stump, neatly flicked around the corner
drifts onto leg stump again, this time it's placed well and backward square can't stop the two
dropped, almost the breakthrough as Mascarenhas pops a return catch down the pitch, Pollard goes with one one hand and can't hold on as he hits the ground
on off stump, defended down the pitch
taken from outside off, into the leg side
gives himself a hint of room, cuts hard out to the cover sweeper
dragged down short, doesn't get up very much but Strauss manages to pull it through midwicket
pushed back to the bowler
can't beat Miller on the leg side this time as he sprints across from his delivery stride to save the run...excellent commitment from the bowler
cut away square through the off side, made a slightly louder crack off the bat
keeps low on middle and leg, pushed through midwicket
finds the gap at point again
defended with a straight bat back to the bowler
too wide, slapped through the covers but it's just the single...lack of pace didn't help Mascarenhas there
driven through the covers off the back foot, sensible batting in that over
tucked out to midwicket
well well, brings out the switch hit (I think) and there's an appeal from Miller but it probably struck outside leg stump...he's not quite Kevin Pietersen
worked down the ground and good running brings two
tries a reverse sweep again, doesn't make contact
well placed through the leg side again, two more with some hard running

calamity for England, Strauss whips it to midwicket where Gayle makes a good save. Strauss is already down at the other end having not talked to Mascarenhas (who was doing a bit of ball watching) and he's the one that has to go and he isn't best pleased
cut away out to deep cover
worked into the leg side, wide enough of Gayle this time for a single
nearly a return catch, Strauss bunts this back down the pitch but it reaches Pollard on the half volley
picks the gap, too wide from Pollard and Strauss places it between cover and mid off for a welcome boundary
beaten by the low bounce, goes for the pull and Ramdin makes a good take but feels the pain at the same time
chopped away down to third man
worked through square leg
comes forward, opens the face and dabs it to backward point
big appeal as Strauss is struck by a full ball, but he got a nice inside edge on it
pushed down to long on
makes this into a full toss, clips it out to deep square-leg

and that's the end of Broad, a limp chip shot back to the bowler who snaffles it easily. Broad tried to turn it to leg and just got a leading edge back down the pitch. Miller deserved that and the end is near for England
short, wide and cut with immense power! I don't know why I put an exclamation mark! But I did!
driven back hard to the bowler
Strauss works it for a single to leg
another leg-side flick
lines up a cover drive before dragging it to mid-on
outside leg, off his pads
quicker ball bunted to mid-on who mis-fields
defended on the front foot by Batty
driven out to cover by the Batty
nice, straight delivery but Batty can't do much with it
runs for Batty! He's off the mark with a crunching back-foot drive. Quality batty from Batty
reverse-swept powerfully to extra cover.
reverse swept
shot Batty! Short, wide and cut hard for four. Monstrous shot, and Gareth's now got his highest score in international cricket
Batty - oh Batty. Batty's run himself out here. Nudges this to mid-on where Miller doth lurk, and he wings down a very sharp throw which leaves our man short of his ground
swept to leg
flicked off his toes
turned off his toes
worked to leg
super sweep from Harmison, collecting it from wide of the off stump and paddling it around with cheeky intent
Strauss walks into a nudge to mid-on
another nudge and Miller dives spectacularly to his left to field...colliding with Harmison
thick outside edge and Strauss calls him through for a single. In comes the throw to the non-striker's end which was too wide, and despite Miller's best efforts, Harmison is home
turned off his pads and they lunge two. Strauss is really puffing now
dropped dead to the off side and they sprint for a single as a matter of course. A default fight-or-flight response to tailend batting and, somehow, Harmison isn't run-out
goes for a sweep but misses against this straight and slow, loopy delivery
off the back foot, he leans back and carves it over cover
slapped to long-off, but only for a single
chipped just short of long-off
swept to fine-leg
low full toss and here comes Pollard in at deep midwicket, he should take this comfortably - but he's slipped! Calamity Jane and it's four
crunched to mid-off
sweeps from outside off
reverse sweep but only for a single
sweeps to short fine-leg - oh dear, the run-out's on here! But Strauss is quick
nobbled to leg and he steals the strike
quicker ball hurries Strauss into a push out to the off side
a dabby, paddly sweep and he gets the single
tries to squeeze it past the short third man
worked to leg
steps outside leg to cry and clump it over cover, but drags it to short midwicket. They get a single - just, though he'd have been run-out by a mile had the throw been in target
very full and Harmison can only get a single to long-on
drilled down the ground for two - really well played
Bravo raps him on the pads as he tries to whip it to leg but it's outside off
down leg, Strauss follows it and nobbles it around the corner
outside off, he swings and misses
slower ball but he can only get a single to short midwicket
Strauss tries to flip this over the keeper but only grabs a single
crashed through cover for two, bringing up his third one-day hundred
slashed through extra cover for four!
down leg, Harmison threatens to run but Pollard sends him back
bowled him! Bowled him! Pollard pumps his fist as he knocks out Strauss's leg stump
good, straight ball but Anderson turns it to leg. Here comes the throw - Harmison is miles short here but there's a misfield at the stumps!
clipped to leg for another neat and pretty single. England need ugly fours and sixes
down the leg side, nudged, but Ramdin collects
clipped off his toes
nice and full, dug out - nothing Harmison can do with that
a quicker full toss and somehow Ramdin stops it - getting his body in the way. Great work
steps outside leg and threads it through cover! Top shot.
full and pretty straight...but not straight enough apparently for an lbw
clumped to square leg
too full, Harmison tries to smash it through the covers but gets a bottom edge
down the leg side - and a wide!
bowled him! Brilliant slower ball completely foxes Anderson's attempt to smack it over midwicket, and that's game, set and match to West Indies
